dsDescriptionValue.value:
This dataset is collected from Douyu("https://www.douyu.com"), a crowdsourced live video streaming platform in China, where viewers can post Danmu while watching live video. It refers to a commentary sharing mechanism in which a viewer can post comments directly on the video frames when watching it, and the comments will slide over the video screen from right to left in real time. Besides posting comments, Douyu allows viewers to donate monetary virtual gifts to broadcasters. The dataset contains 3 types of data:
  • Danmu: the comment text posted by a viewer in the channel, as well as the timestamp and ID of the viewer who posts Danmu
  • Gift Donating: gift donating event in the channel, and contains the information such as timestamp, the donating viewerâ€™s ID, and gift ID
  • Online Viewer: number of viewers in the channel
The `README` file in dataset contains detailed explanation of files and fields.

publicationCitation.value: Xiaodong Wang, Ye Tian, Rongheng Lan, Wen Yang, Xinming Zhang, "Beyond the watching: Understanding viewer interactions in crowdsourced live video broadcasting services", IEEE Trans. on Circuits & Systems for Video Technology
